-- Dassault, Thales Negotiating Libya Military-Equipment Orders, Tribune Says
-- David Whitehouse
-- 2010-07-23T04:52:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/dassault-aviation-thales-are-negotiating-libya-contracts-la-tribune-says.html

          
          
             Dassault Aviation SA and Thales SA
are in talks over air-defense contracts with the Libyan
government, French daily La Tribune reported, citing
unidentified people.  
 Dassault is in negotiations to supply an initial batch of
14 Rafale planes equipped with Mica missiles, the newspaper
said. The Thales contract would be for radar and communication
systems, according to La Tribune.  
          
          


  


        